<br>
Seventh moon 1346....<br>
<br>
On the day of my birth,I was betrothed to man I did not know.A great warrior's son I was told later. He was only 2 at the time. On that day and many days after this it distraught me naught.Throughout my youth my world was surrounded by magic.My mother a great High Elf Enchantress of many years old ,whose abilities to charm and calm surpassed no other.Her talks of quests and battles she had fought held many exciting and sleepless nights for me.My father a master  High Elf Wizard, described places of beauty and horror , places where Wizards dared to bring an adventuring party and also  stories of battle and slaying many a dragon and gods ,I was held in such awe.These things they spoke of I believed where waiting for me.... We lived in a small castle next to Elizerain Lake, safe from foes.It was isolated ,however my parents sought to educate me reading old scrolls practicing the arcane science's,and  I was taught some magic by both parents.The Lake was enchanting(My mother and her magic I believe) and  all the unicorns from Lesser Faydark would come drink from the lake on every full moon.How beautiful they are to watch... Now being one and twenty my distraught had come full circle..I am to wed this warriors son and live my life as a wife.My future that I dreamed to be ,was only that, a dream..I have to write all these thoughts for there is no one to listen... Now I have decided that because of Pride,and my ways of solitude and silence that I would make a terrible wife... <br>
<br>
Ninth moon 1346<br>
It is the night before the ceremony and I have decided to run away..I will miss my home and I know dangers await but I have to..I have to learn the ways of magic..And have my life be what I only dreamed it could be....I packed my satchel and stared out the window as a party of 8 men arrived on horseback. I cast a simple spell of invisibility  and then climbed out onto  the windows ledge. I climbed down and my bare feet were silent on the cool earth. I dashed out into the woods holding my hand over my mouth to silence my fast breaths. I stopped next to a tree , looking back at my home, the only home I had ever known. Inside, my husband to be was waiting, my mother making preparations.  In the stillness of the woods a chill washed over my flesh , my heart began to beat faster. The woods rustled, I looked about and what I saw made my knees falter and skin go white.<br>
   Dog beasts, upright, a big party of them moving quietly. I heard there  growling dialect..&quot; The old warrior ..is here..&quot;<br>
A large one wearing a crown with fangs as long as her hand  spoke menacingly &quot;Kill them all ..&quot;<br>
       I began to run , towards my home to warn of this attack, what could I do what could I say. I ran into the courtyard and began to yell &quot;Dogbeasts in the woods!! &quot;<br>
 The spell I had cast had vanished and there I stood guilty with my knapsack. I rushed into the kitchen my mother pacing<br>
&quot;Mother quickly we must leave dogbeasts in the woods!! there going to Attack&quot; She looked stunned ,but she rushed out of the room. I sat there unmoving not knowing what to do. My father rushed in and handed me a vial.&quot; Drink this , it is from one of our guests, drink it quickly, you are not safe here..&quot;<br>
  &quot; But father where will  I go what about you and mother and..&quot;<br>
&quot;Drink it I say!!! &quot;<br>
I brought it to my lips and drank it. Soon the room grew foggy ,my gaze clouded. My vision in a moment cleared and I found myself staring down at a path of ice...<br>
